Two bug fixes for the diff viewer.

## Bug 1 — Hunk count shows "1 of 1 change" regardless of actual hunks

The FloatingNav is showing the wrong hunk count. It is collapsing all
changes into a single hunk instead of grouping them correctly.

A hunk is a contiguous block of changes. Two change blocks separated by
unchanged lines are two separate hunks.

Fix the hunk detection logic in DiffViewer. Hunks should be computed
from the diff result by grouping contiguous changed lines (added or
removed) separated by unchanged lines into distinct hunk objects.

Each hunk should have:
  - startIndex: number  (row index of first changed line)
  - endIndex: number    (row index of last changed line)

FloatingNav receives the correct hunk array and navigates between them.

Test with code-1.ts and code-2.ts — should show "1 of 6 changes" or
similar, not "1 of 1 change".

## Bug 2 — Long lines truncated in right panel

Long lines in the right panel are cut off without horizontal scroll.
Each panel needs independent horizontal scroll when line content exceeds
panel width.

Fix:
- Each panel in SplitPane should have overflow-x: auto
- Line content must not wrap — white-space: nowrap on each line
- Horizontal scroll must be independent per panel (not synced)
- Vertical scroll remains synced between panels

## Tests
- Add Vitest cases for hunk grouping logic:
  - Single contiguous block = 1 hunk
  - Two blocks separated by unchanged lines = 2 hunks
  - All lines changed = 1 hunk
  - No changes = 0 hunks
  - Alternating changed/unchanged lines = correct hunk count

Do not change any interfaces in src/core/interfaces/.
No any types.
All errors via Result<T, AppError>.


