⏺ Both bugs are fixed and committed:

  Bug 1 — Hunk count: computeViewHunks(leftRows) now scans the rendered panel rows directly and groups contiguous non-context rows into ViewHunk objects. FloatingNav uses these
  instead of the structuredPatch hunks that were merging nearby change blocks. 6 new Vitest cases cover the edge cases (no changes, single block, two separated blocks,
  all-changed, placeholders, alternating).

  Bug 2 — Long-line truncation: .line gets min-width: max-content so the row never shrinks below its content width, and .lineContent uses flex: 1 0 auto (flex-shrink: 0) so it
  stops being compressed by the flex container.
